The paper deals with the transportation cost metric on probability measures supported on a grid in $\R^2$. This suggests that the paper is likely to be related to topics in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of Fourier analytic techniques also suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the distortion of embeddings, which is a common topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
